                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/3086</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-16T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>520. [For <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d243fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">J. C. Grew</persName>, Chargé in Austria-Hungary
                        from Apr. 7 to 14, departed on the latter date for Berne, Switzerland,
                        accompanied by the entire Embassy staff.</note>]:</p>
                <p>Your 1817, 7th, and 1836, 14th. If the Austro-Hungarian Government will eliminate
                    the restriction of four weeks for the departure of American citizens mentioned
                    in paragraph 1 and will add to paragraph 3 the words “or a menace to the
                    national safety,” this Government will accept the proposed reciprocal
                    arrangement. It will be observed that paragraph 2 is unnecessary and should be
                    eliminated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
